comment: Oh man, so I'm just now finding out about these new Apple headphones Max or whatevers.
For metal headphones, that don't fold, and require a bullshit proprietary case that doesn't protect anything.
A proprietary case that's required and doesn't actually protect anything may in fact be the most Apple thing Apple has ever done.
(For those not in the know, the headphones don't have a power button/switch and require the case to actually turn off. So they'll bleed life if you don't put them in the case or lose it.)
The case also has a battery in it, so like ya know with iphone batteries eventually
The metal bit is also pretty dumbfounding. Metal is heavy yo. You don't want heavy headphones. Fatigue is real.
Heaviest set of cans I have are my Shure SRH 840's and those things are just short of 320g. Can't wear em for barely more than an hour.
MAX pods are almost 400g. Can't even imagine that sitting on my skull for long periods.
